{"art": [{"brightcove": "", "caption": "Conservative talk show host Rush Limbaugh at a 2007 Michigan event. A recent survey found his show broadly mistrusted among 36 news sources. (Getty Images)", "id": 5392, "infogram": "", "ndn": "", "ndnid": "", "other": "", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/photos/Limbaugh_2007_event.jpg", "resource_type": {"id": 1, "name": "Photo", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/mediatype/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/media/5392/", "title": "Limbaugh public speech 2007", "wibbitz": "", "youtube": "", "youtubeID": ""}], "author": [{"email_address": "jgreenberg@politifact.com", "first_name": "Jon", "id": 257, "last_name": "Greenberg", "name_slug": "jon-greenberg", "on_staff_page": 5, "phone": "", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots16.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/257/", "title": "Staff Writer", "twitter": "JonZGreenberg"}], "canonical_url": "/punditfact/statements/2014/nov/06/leonard-pitts-jr/liberal-columnist-says-least-trusted-news-sources-/", "edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Punditfact", "edition": "PunditFact", "edition_slug": "punditfact", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 48, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The PunditFact Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/48/"}, "editor": [{"email_address": "asharockman@politifact.com", "first_name": "Aaron", "id": 114, "last_name": "Sharockman", "name_slug": "aaron-sharockman", "on_staff_page": 2, "phone": "727-553-4534", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots05.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/114/", "title": "Executive Director", "twitter": "asharock"}], "facebook_headline": null, "id": 10195, "in_future": false, "is_pundit": true, "make_public": true, "preview": true, "researcher": [{"email_address": "jgreenberg@politifact.com", "first_name": "Jon", "id": 257, "last_name": "Greenberg", "name_slug": "jon-greenberg", "on_staff_page": 5, "phone": "", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots16.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/257/", "title": "Staff Writer", "twitter": "JonZGreenberg"}], "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statement/10195/", "ruling": {"adkey": "Truth-O-Meter", "advalue": "Half True", "id": 3, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementruling/3/", "ruling": "Half-True", "ruling_graphic": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/rulings/tom-halftrue.png", "ruling_slug": "half-true"}, "ruling_comments": "<p>Many words have been said and many numbers crunched to explain political polarization in America. One theory is that liberals and conservatives swim in different waters when it comes to news and information. Liberal columnist Leonard Pitts, Jr. offered a new spin on this theme. In a <a href=\"http://www.miamiherald.com/opinion/opn-columns-blogs/leonard-pitts-jr/article3499672.html\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"><u>Nov.1 op-ed</u></a>, Pitt said most of the fault lies on the right end of the spectrum. He blamed conservative hardliners who &quot;are more rabid in support of those who validate their views than the rest of us are in pursuit of simple truth.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To prove his point, Pitts cited a <a href=\"http://www.journalism.org/files/2014/10/Political-Polarization-and-Media-Habits-FINAL-REPORT-10-21-2014.pdf\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"><u>recent report from the Pew Research Center</u></a> that explored the level of trust enjoyed by 36 news sources, ranging from television networks to partisan blogs. Pitts focused his column<strong> </strong>on two sources, Rush Limbaugh and Fox News. In the Pew study, 39 percent of respondents said they distrusted Limbaugh, and 37 percent voiced the same misgivings about Fox News.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pitts noted that Rush Limbaugh &quot;hosts the number one show on radio and Fox is the highest-rated cable news outlet.&quot; His conclusion?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;America&rsquo;s least-trusted news sources are also its most popular.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A reader asked us to check that statement and we are happy to oblige.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two elements to check: Are Limbaugh and Fox News the least-trusted? And are they the most popular with Americans?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&lsquo;Least-trusted&rsquo;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, the Pew survey found that more people distrusted Limbaugh and Fox News than any other outlet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But that doesn&rsquo;t necessarily mean that the two outlets are the &quot;least-trusted&quot; as Pitts claimed. To find that out, you need to account for the percentage of people who say that they trust Limbaugh and Fox News.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For instance, while 39 percent of respondents said they distrusted Limbaugh, 12 percent said they trust him. And for Fox News, more people (44 percent) said they trust the network then said they distrust it (37 percent).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Factoring that in, Limbaugh has the biggest trust gap of any of the 36 outlets polled. But Fox News is in the middle of the pack.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s the calculation for each outlet in the survey.</p>\r\n\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left:0pt;\">\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:none; width:600px\">\r\n\t<tbody>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>News Source</strong></p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Pct. Trust</strong></p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Pct. Distrust</strong></p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Net trust</strong></p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">CNN</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">54%</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">20%</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">+34</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">ABC</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">50%</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">17</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">+33</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">NBC</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">50%</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">19%</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">+31</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">CBS</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">46%</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:middle\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">17%</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertica